# AppBar Component Usage

## Overview
Feature pages in HomeSynchronicity use the Syncfusion AppBar component for consistent page headers.

## When to Use AppBar
Use AppBar on all major feature pages:
- ✅ Dashboard, Accounts, Bills, Budgets
- ✅ Profile, Settings
- ✅ Healthcare, Insurance
- ✅ Inventory, Maintenance, Documents
- ✅ Financial overview pages

## Implementation Pattern

### Basic AppBar (Title Only)
```html
<ejs-appbar cssClass="custom-appbar">
  <ng-template #content>
    <div class="appbar-content">
      <div class="appbar-title">
        <h4 class="mb-0">🏦 Page Title</h4>
        <small class="text-muted">Page description or subtitle</small>
      </div>
    </div>
  </ng-template>
</ejs-appbar>
```

### AppBar with Actions
```html
<ejs-appbar cssClass="custom-appbar">
  <span class="appbar-title">🏦 Accounts Hub</span>
  <div class="e-appbar-spacer"></div>
  <button ejs-button cssClass="e-inherit" (click)="openDialog()">
    + Add Account
  </button>
  <button ejs-button cssClass="e-inherit" (click)="openOtherDialog()">
    + Add Item
  </button>
</ejs-appbar>
```

## Required Import
```typescript
import { AppBarModule } from '@syncfusion/ej2-angular-navigations';

@Component({
  imports: [
    // ... other imports
    AppBarModule
  ]
})
```

## Styling

### Global AppBar Styles
AppBar should use the teal gradient theme:
```scss
::ng-deep .custom-appbar {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #108E91 0%, #20B6AA 100%);
  color: white;
  margin-bottom: 20px;

  .appbar-content {
    padding: 15px 20px;
  }

  .appbar-title {
    h4 {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: white;
    }

    small {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
      font-size: 13px;
    }
  }
}
```

